{"key":"post-10055636","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>10055636</id>\n<content>&lt;/font&gt;&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;font class=&quot;small&quot;&gt;Quote:&lt;/font&gt;&lt;hr /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;im prepping my other bulk subs by pouring boiling water over hpoo/coir/coffee/verm/gypsum into a 5gallon bucket. shaking it around once everything is hydrated to mix it well w/out putting my hands into it...&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;hr /&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&lt;font class=&quot;post&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;That's not an appropriate method of pasteurization.&amp;nbsp; What it is, is a half assed attempt at sterilization, but probably accomplishes neither.&amp;nbsp; Coir is very inhospitable to fungi spore germination, thus it can be mis-pasteurized and still grow certain species of mushrooms, but that isn't true for straw.&amp;nbsp; I'd suggest getting your pasteurization bath to the correct temperature and THEN adding the straw.&amp;nbsp; Keep it in the 140F to 160F range for an hour.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Pre-hydration is very important.&amp;nbsp; The straw won't properly hydrate during the pasteurization process.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Your 1&quot; pieces are too small and the structure of the straw has been destroyed.&amp;nbsp; You want 1&quot; minimum pieces going up to 4&quot; to 6&quot; in length.&amp;nbsp; I'd suggest putting your straw in a cardboard box or rubbermaid tote and go after it with a weed whacker.&amp;nbsp; Stop after about 30 seconds so you still have some long pieces.&amp;nbsp; You want the mycelium to colonize the inside of the straw, and also to leave the inside intact, which is a major moisture reservoir, as you can see from the microscope picture of a cross section of straw below.&lt;br /&gt;RR&lt;br /&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://files.shroomery.org/files/07-006/108452877-SEM_of_Straw.jpg&quot; class=&quot;highslide&quot; onclick=&quot;return hs.expand(this,{slideshowGroup:'hsg1'})&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;&lt;img style=&quot;max-width:192px;height:auto;&quot; src=&quot;/forums/thumbs/07-006/108452877-thumb_SEM_of_Straw.jpg&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>10055670</next>\n<prev>10055547</prev>\n<first>10054753</first>\n<last>10058496</last>\n<when>1238198607</when>\n<utime>03/28/09 03:03 AM</utime>\n</post>"}